Serves: 4Ingredients:400g flour4 large eggsSemolina, for dustingMethod:1) Sift the flour into a bowl and make a well in the centre. Place the eggs in the well and draw in the flour, mixing until you have a smooth dough.2) Knead until elastic, cover in lightly oiled plastic and leave to rest at room temperature for 30 minutes.3) Sprinkle semolina on a counter and roll out the dough to your desired thickness, flipping and rolling to increase the elasticity. Cut strips or shapes according to your recipe.4) Cook the pasta in salted boiling water for 2-3 minutes, drain and serve with your favourite pasta sauce.DIFFERENT PASTA SHAPES YOU CAN MAKE: Linguine: If cutting thin strands for linguine, roll a sheet of dough up like a Swiss roll and use a sharp knife to cut it into thin slices. Stracci: Roll the dough out thinly and cut into rough 'rag' strips. Lasagna: Roll the dough out thinly and cut into rectangular 'sheets'. Pappardelle: Roll the dough out thinly and cut into wide strips with a pastry wheel.